# Claude Code statusline — shellcheck config
#
# Scope: applies to bin/cc-statusline.sh (the published bash entrypoint) and
# the bats test suite under tests/.
#
# Policy:
#   - Shell dialect is pinned to bash (shebang is `#!/usr/bin/env bash`); the
#     script targets Bash 3.2+ to stay compatible with stock macOS bash.
#   - We run shellcheck with its default rule set. No rules are disabled
#     globally — if a finding is intentional, suppress it *inline* with a
#     `# shellcheck disable=SCxxxx  <reason>` comment directly above the
#     offending line, so the justification travels with the code.
#   - Rules that enforce strict-bash style (SC2292 [[ ]] over [ ], SC2250
#     ${var} braces, SC2248 quoting, SC2312 masked pipe returns, etc.) are
#     part of the optional `all` group and are intentionally NOT enabled,
#     because:
#       1. The script was originally written as plain POSIX-ish bash 3.2 and
#          rewriting every `[ ]` as `[[ ]]` is churn without benefit.
#       2. Turning them on now would mask the defaults-clean baseline that
#          CI enforces.
#     If a future contributor wants to opt in locally, run
#     `shellcheck -o all bin/cc-statusline.sh` explicitly.
#
# Keep this file minimal. Add entries only with a justification comment.

shell=bash
